[
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.1",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "My son, if thou be surety for thy friend, {if} thou hast stricken thy hand with a stranger,",
    "hash": "9066c1831a309da09fc4138b1158639dd0360dfb6183010bd5e3aba9ff73d2a7"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.2",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "Thou art snared with the words of thy mouth, thou art taken with the words of thy mouth.",
    "hash": "7bd411b67dcdd7f2a10c12be849e078d48eb5fd1287a674ed6ebcd6440bafe3f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.3",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "Do this now, my son, and deliver thyself, when thou art come into the hand of thy friend; go, humble thyself, and make sure thy friend. {and make...: or, so shalt thou prevail with thy friend}",
    "hash": "5138b0e95507db9e9dea0595629de03b8e2faa7a132b8ef7e4ea2846c16f30b8"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.4",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "Give not sleep to thine eyes, nor slumber to thine eyelids.",
    "hash": "a0213410ee8be65d0aa2db4d108f0ab6a9843efb000b2c26442862deb436fbda"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.5",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "Deliver thyself as a roe from the hand {of the hunter}, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.",
    "hash": "fee833e91ecc99e3a7d5f5299c1d2b0c65ae8435be0776e0b0bbb67eb8756c62"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.6",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Go to the ant, thou sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise:",
    "hash": "9ef35bd5f4e3b4fab8d80630dddc65c73f80b9f81b854cdecb81885a4a71ef52"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.7",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Which having no guide, overseer, or ruler,",
    "hash": "b657b3be27e6666bb499ecee10c59913b0d2f0dd047faece8e43cf2ebacc656b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.8",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "Provideth her meat in the summer, {and} gathereth her food in the harvest.",
    "hash": "815367c82e8a2ae5dac79bc168d7256bc2f95e9374844440fcaf47823d7f2cb8"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.9",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "How long wilt thou sleep, O sluggard? when wilt thou arise out of thy sleep?",
    "hash": "055f201beb7a9c690a4d4258df712cf5227cedad8f7c8ef61ef188f28ea4aee9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.10",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "{Yet} a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:",
    "hash": "6e8a860f41d4868d354c3e20cf6cb69a8916bd96b1b578e16856d4ef80739828"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.11",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "So shall thy poverty come as one that travelleth, and thy want as an armed man.",
    "hash": "fb2b0701bfcd61360b8c26cd497afac4fbdd5619bf27c8d5d86adc52b0503303"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.12",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "A naughty person, a wicked man, walketh with a froward mouth.",
    "hash": "61bbef1a450d4c48a0321990837e16c84ac88a24bf0f4f1adbd6ff99a9bf3dd3"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.13",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "He winketh with his eyes, he speaketh with his feet, he teacheth with his fingers;",
    "hash": "d791055fa3ed0cfa85ece54acf0fcc7f40e869045b830e630ae1f5edb6a91d5e"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.14",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "Frowardness {is} in his heart, he deviseth mischief continually; he soweth discord. {soweth: Heb. casteth forth}",
    "hash": "610e25a126c53932fc0d0bc628aec113129e8711ef264f9c334466576c8ce773"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.15",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.",
    "hash": "e8e5c23f7407d7d039ceeb06003a332c0616a32fee1cd3e7d41512a025d3bff4"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.16",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "These six {things} doth the LORD hate: yea, seven {are} an abomination unto him: {unto...: Heb. of his soul}",
    "hash": "700efd79901b300cedb69b55b4ed195d8523b5041538e4c2dfa7a99e13a72a91"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.17",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood, {A proud...: Heb. Haughty eyes}",
    "hash": "cb2acda729f8879196164b53eff5d2f48fa4ab590353f0e00e3516d55a43dbe1"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.18",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "An heart that deviseth wicked imaginations, feet that be swift in running to mischief,",
    "hash": "ecfab2e8d300b718032774476b2bcae5f45665be8f288ea6cd651e88bf6b5e60"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.19",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "A false witness {that} speaketh lies, and he that soweth discord among brethren.",
    "hash": "6a82b0db5320b1870eba57c374d8e9ac5cb319d93d0fa2f2c5c392345bc27944"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.20",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "My son, keep thy father's commandment, and forsake not the law of thy mother:",
    "hash": "c089109176e1c09d495d1b17549a21b9ea7201046b2f31ba0a2c95283f9dacaf"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.21",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Bind them continually upon thine heart, {and} tie them about thy neck.",
    "hash": "8251c674f1db51e4757f5b573d15501d80a5ef91e17828f24ef5f22822e6e38a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.22",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "When thou goest, it shall lead thee; when thou sleepest, it shall keep thee; and {when} thou awakest, it shall talk with thee.",
    "hash": "8fc5eceda6c04a873c03b4970d6eb3614f2f275861b25621d1d002c6c1ca47df"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.23",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "For the commandment {is} a lamp; and the law {is} light; and reproofs of instruction {are} the way of life: {lamp: or, candle}",
    "hash": "3ebe3b0b4e884ebe69752c4113a43bbd13ed0360e5d46891276a19527bcc0027"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.24",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "To keep thee from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a strange woman. {of the...: or, of the strange tongue}",
    "hash": "8524cca6ce789009ed66cc7c7d9bb9bdd9c92fbe558ee02032eaa87b7cacc761"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.25",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Lust not after her beauty in thine heart; neither let her take thee with her eyelids.",
    "hash": "3dbf4d41df95eab123f02ee6298d3309544f6285ce877a4641bf7097573ba1b8"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.26",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "For by means of a whorish woman {a man is brought} to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will hunt for the precious life. {the adulteress: Heb. the woman of a man, or, a man's wife}",
    "hash": "af29884177fb948ba207dc5212d6e5629e96d21a388cce40f0de87b74aee560c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.27",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?",
    "hash": "c0e477f54a0ee9bcf81fe2da59d1481e36464000c5fae27a677847dd3250d768"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.28",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "Can one go upon hot coals, and his feet not be burned?",
    "hash": "1fc9edb0960ea28630744a7315ef6376dff37138164647d31e9adc93147359c2"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.29",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 29,
    "text": "So he that goeth in to his neighbour's wife; whosoever toucheth her shall not be innocent.",
    "hash": "d349b071b8c73b1e6ba3afbf3b9d4ebbde5539faf71f87be37e297582c7e5cf8"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.30",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 30,
    "text": "{Men} do not despise a thief, if he steal to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;",
    "hash": "b9b33db7c3a2ccbe7243558a1ce4fc0ee945091fdf46c89f4af15334051cf074"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.31",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 31,
    "text": "But {if} he be found, he shall restore sevenfold; he shall give all the substance of his house.",
    "hash": "111a39b4b188afb204aa29337d73538b6cee0dcf2f5f804000607a75ff1ae8d5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.32",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 32,
    "text": "{But} whoso committeth adultery with a woman lacketh understanding: he {that} doeth it destroyeth his own soul. {understanding: Heb. heart}",
    "hash": "9b0464e5f51703061ebc53f617aaba4210d83b554f1770fd28f3d851c5d8550c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.33",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 33,
    "text": "A wound and dishonour shall he get; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.",
    "hash": "2c000df98041b51044a91046c0bcd768223539f9af680cb5aa99de29fc2c00c8"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.34",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 34,
    "text": "For jealousy {is} the rage of a man: therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.",
    "hash": "567e13a422c73fb6980275794211ef1363f0655efe480dc076b9a6ac5119655c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PRO.6.35",
    "book": "Proverbs",
    "bookNum": 20,
    "bookAbbrev": "PRO",
    "chapter": 6,
    "verse": 35,
    "text": "He will not regard any ransom; neither will he rest content, though thou givest many gifts. {He will...: Heb. He will not accept the face of any ransom}",
    "hash": "cf7183cf0d75505c235b636570606dc70574f0acf86bf7431ae403a196d3e3e1"
  }
]